<Callout type="tip" title="The bar graph on a DMM bridges the gap">
  Most professional DMMs include an analogue bar graph display that updates at 40–50 times per second — much faster than the digit update rate. For most dynamic signal observation tasks, this provides the "needle-like" trend visibility of an AVM while retaining the accuracy and features of a digital instrument. If you regularly watch changing signals, prioritise a DMM with a large, fast bar graph display.
</Callout>

